WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.440
We're so pleased to have, as I said, Bernard and Betsy here at church with us this morning.

2
00:00:06.440 --> 00:00:12.840
And I first met Bernard in England, and he was coming to Stoke-on-Trent.

3
00:00:12.840 --> 00:00:18.000
This is what, 16, 17 years ago, something like that, where we were living.

4
00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:24.720
And there was like an evangelistic mission where you could bring folks who were non-Christians,

5
00:00:24.720 --> 00:00:26.760
who wanted to hear more about the Christian faith to come.

6
00:00:26.760 --> 00:00:33.200
And I remember bringing friends to that, and Bernard was the one who faithfully preached the Gospel that day.

7
00:00:33.200 --> 00:00:38.200
And full circle, the Lord has brought us both to Birmingham.

8
00:00:38.200 --> 00:00:43.000
I'm from here, but Bernard, where are you from?

9
00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:50.600
I am not from here, as you'll quickly be able to see from my British accent.

10
00:00:50.640 --> 00:00:53.640
So I, thank you Julia.

11
00:00:53.640 --> 00:01:01.600
I am from London, England, and I moved to New York in 2012.

12
00:01:01.600 --> 00:01:05.960
And a few years afterwards, met Betsy.

13
00:01:05.960 --> 00:01:08.040
We got married in 2015.

14
00:01:08.040 --> 00:01:16.960
And then in 2023, Betsy pulled me back to her hometown of Birmingham.

15
00:01:16.960 --> 00:01:20.600
And very happily so, I'm very happy to be here.

16
00:01:20.600 --> 00:01:22.600
It's great to be here in Alabama.

17
00:01:22.600 --> 00:01:25.600
We're glad to have you here.

18
00:01:25.600 --> 00:01:32.000
Could you maybe tell us, I mean, when Julia and I are out, people hear her accent.

19
00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:35.080
And they say, OK, well, where did you meet?

20
00:01:35.080 --> 00:01:36.920
How did you end up here?

21
00:01:36.920 --> 00:01:39.880
You both have an interesting, everybody's story of how they met is interesting.

22
00:01:39.880 --> 00:01:42.760
But you guys have an interesting story about how you met.

23
00:01:42.760 --> 00:01:43.760
How did you meet?

24
00:01:43.760 --> 00:01:49.720
Well, Betsy wrote an article for a website called the Gospel Coalition.

25
00:01:49.720 --> 00:01:54.040
And it was an article about singleness, being single.

26
00:01:54.040 --> 00:01:56.480
And I was single.

27
00:01:56.480 --> 00:02:02.160
I read this article about Betsy, written by Betsy, about her being single.

28
00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:08.760
And I did a little googling and found her email address.

29
00:02:08.760 --> 00:02:10.600
And I sent her an email.

30
00:02:10.600 --> 00:02:13.320
And she replied.

31
00:02:13.320 --> 00:02:16.040
That was the important part.

32
00:02:16.040 --> 00:02:22.600
And then we started emailing and video calling.

33
00:02:22.600 --> 00:02:28.000
And then I flew down to Birmingham to take her out on a date.

34
00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:31.520
Pretty expensive first date right there.

35
00:02:31.520 --> 00:02:32.640
But it went very well.

36
00:02:32.640 --> 00:02:34.240
And we kept dating.

37
00:02:34.240 --> 00:02:39.080
And a year later, got married a year after I read that article.

38
00:02:39.080 --> 00:02:40.560
Praise God.

39
00:02:40.600 --> 00:02:41.480
Absolutely.

40
00:02:41.480 --> 00:02:45.360
Yeah, it's wonderful that you're both here.

41
00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:46.960
And the Lord's used you in different ways.

42
00:02:46.960 --> 00:02:51.840
I mentioned you preaching the gospel in stoke and been involved in church planting and pastoring.

43
00:02:51.840 --> 00:02:55.680
But you didn't grow up in a Christian household.

44
00:02:55.680 --> 00:03:02.720
So I'd love for you to share more about what life was like growing up for you and in your background.

45
00:03:02.720 --> 00:03:06.040
And then eventually, how did you end up coming to faith?

46
00:03:06.040 --> 00:03:06.640
Sure.

47
00:03:06.640 --> 00:03:09.600
I am from a Jewish background.

48
00:03:09.600 --> 00:03:17.480
Pretty what's known as liberal Jewish, which basically means bacon at the weekends is fine if you're liberal Jewish.

49
00:03:17.480 --> 00:03:23.520
So we literally have bacon at the weekends and enjoy it.

50
00:03:23.520 --> 00:03:31.760
And synagogue a few times a year, two or three times a year at most.

51
00:03:31.760 --> 00:03:37.120
But I did go through the bar mitzvah process, which you do when you're 13.

52
00:03:37.120 --> 00:03:45.320
And that was that was quite important to me because after going through that, I said to myself, there's nothing there.

53
00:03:45.320 --> 00:03:47.600
It's just it's just dry ritual.

54
00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:49.680
There's no there are no big answers.

55
00:03:49.680 --> 00:03:52.560
I'm not getting the meaning of life here.

56
00:03:52.560 --> 00:04:00.560
So I then started to look elsewhere and I went to my high schools little Christian group.

57
00:04:00.600 --> 00:04:08.320
There are 1,250 kids at my high school and about 20 or 30 at the little Christian group.

58
00:04:08.320 --> 00:04:15.440
But there I had the I actually had this same passage that I'll be preaching on later.

59
00:04:15.440 --> 00:04:19.000
The speaker was on the same passage.

60
00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:21.960
And I don't think I'd ever heard the gospel before.

61
00:04:21.960 --> 00:04:28.840
It was very fresh and very wonderful, particularly the message of eternal life.

62
00:04:28.840 --> 00:04:42.360
That was what really gripped me because I'd sort of in teenagers have time to think and I'd reach the view that if we all die and then we're forgotten, what is the point?

63
00:04:42.360 --> 00:04:45.200
And that really bothered me, really bothered me.

64
00:04:45.200 --> 00:04:51.000
So to hear that there was a way to live forever through faith in Jesus, that was fantastic news.

65
00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:54.280
I went straight up to the speaker and said, this sounds great, but I'm Jewish.

66
00:04:54.280 --> 00:04:58.080
So, you know, I guess it's not for me.

67
00:04:58.080 --> 00:05:02.160
Fortunately, he was an extremely direct person.

68
00:05:02.160 --> 00:05:04.840
So he said, of course it's for you.

69
00:05:04.840 --> 00:05:06.360
Jesus was Jewish.

70
00:05:06.360 --> 00:05:09.360
If you follow him, you're following your own Messiah.

71
00:05:09.360 --> 00:05:19.040
And he told me about a friend of his who was Jewish and had begun following Jesus and said that he now felt even more Jewish because he was following his own Messiah.

72
00:05:19.040 --> 00:05:20.640
So that was really reassuring.

73
00:05:20.640 --> 00:05:23.880
I needed that direct word.

74
00:05:23.920 --> 00:05:29.680
And I think I think I began following Jesus that night of first hearing the gospel.

75
00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:31.160
Yeah.

76
00:05:31.160 --> 00:05:36.160
Um, so you began growing as a disciple.

77
00:05:36.160 --> 00:05:43.600
The Lord called you into ministry and we're covering a lot of ground and you'd be very happy to speak with folks about ministry involvement.

78
00:05:43.600 --> 00:05:46.760
So you evolved in church planting in Manhattan.

79
00:05:46.760 --> 00:05:50.280
You've been involved in pastoral ministry.

80
00:05:50.280 --> 00:05:57.760
We're a church plant that is almost a year in and we've had conversations and I've kind of picked your brains a little bit about church planting.

81
00:05:57.760 --> 00:06:04.200
I'd love if you could maybe share a little bit of advice for us as a church a year into just getting started.

82
00:06:04.200 --> 00:06:07.960
What would you say to us as a new church family?

83
00:06:07.960 --> 00:06:12.600
Um, well, I think I'd say one thing to you and one thing to the congregation.

84
00:06:12.600 --> 00:06:16.120
So one thing to brand and would be something is going to be hard.

85
00:06:16.160 --> 00:06:27.040
It might be numbers or finances or an issue with the with your venue, your location, your meeting place or something else.

86
00:06:27.040 --> 00:06:30.640
Something will be hard and that is very normal.

87
00:06:30.640 --> 00:06:34.760
Push on through persevere by the grace of God.

88
00:06:34.760 --> 00:06:46.080
And then to the congregation, I think I'd say, please don't expect Trinity Fellowship Church to be providing everything that are fully established.

89
00:06:46.120 --> 00:06:58.000
Long established church will provide the years allow for church members to really bring their gifts to the table and set up programs and just get things.

90
00:06:59.520 --> 00:07:01.440
Tickety boo, do you say that in America?

91
00:07:04.280 --> 00:07:05.240
You know what I mean?

92
00:07:05.240 --> 00:07:06.360
Tickety boo.

93
00:07:07.200 --> 00:07:22.200
But you need to give it time and not expect a newborn church, a very recently planted church to have all the things that a long established church will have.

94
00:07:22.200 --> 00:07:27.720
So put up with some rough and ready stuff along the way.

95
00:07:27.720 --> 00:07:30.560
Be patient with the church.

96
00:07:30.560 --> 00:07:31.880
That's what I would say to you guys.

97
00:07:32.880 --> 00:07:33.720
Thank you so much.

98
00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:35.400
I mean, it may be perfect already.

99
00:07:35.400 --> 00:07:37.280
So that may be unnecessary.

100
00:07:37.280 --> 00:07:38.360
We've got a long ways to go.

101
00:07:41.040 --> 00:07:45.240
What about just right where you're at personally and as a family right now?

102
00:07:45.760 --> 00:07:46.960
How can we be praying for you?

103
00:07:46.960 --> 00:07:50.320
And then I'll turn it over to you to bring God's word to us, but look to pray for you.

104
00:07:50.320 --> 00:07:52.080
Yeah, it'd be great if you could pray.

105
00:07:52.080 --> 00:08:01.120
We went and when we moved to Alabama two years ago, I began pastoring a church in just near Homewood.

106
00:08:02.120 --> 00:08:12.640
And that went on for two years, two good years, but we decided in the end that it probably be best for me to leave that particular

107
00:08:13.240 --> 00:08:14.120
pastorship.

108
00:08:14.600 --> 00:08:19.680
So I stepped down there nothing by the grace of God, nothing disgraceful.

109
00:08:20.120 --> 00:08:22.240
Just wasn't quite the right fit.

110
00:08:23.400 --> 00:08:31.000
So we are between jobs, which I say with faith, because I don't know that there will be another job at the end of it.

111
00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:34.440
But we're praying to God that he'll provide something.

112
00:08:34.800 --> 00:08:35.920
Yeah, absolutely.

113
00:08:36.720 --> 00:08:37.480
Well, let's let's pray.

114
00:08:41.640 --> 00:08:43.480
Lord, great is your faithfulness.

115
00:08:45.040 --> 00:08:48.280
Lord, we know you call us to wait upon you.

116
00:08:49.200 --> 00:08:53.720
And Lord, sometimes that is hard to wait upon you.

117
00:08:54.400 --> 00:08:58.440
But Lord, we thank you that as we wait upon you, we can trust that you are faithful.

118
00:08:59.240 --> 00:09:08.720
And Lord, as we walk by faith, we can trust that you are leading the way and that your goodness and mercy is following us every single day of our lives.

119
00:09:08.720 --> 00:09:11.600
And one day we will dwell in the house of the Lord forever.

120
00:09:12.320 --> 00:09:19.720
And this Lord, I thank you so much for how you have guided and provided for both Bernard and Betsy.

121
00:09:20.480 --> 00:09:31.160
Lord, thank you so much for this wonderful story we've heard of how you brought him to faith in Jesus to embrace Jesus as the Messiah.

122
00:09:31.840 --> 00:09:39.600
And Lord, thank you for how you have led them to each other and led them forward in ministry.

123
00:09:39.840 --> 00:09:46.480
And Lord, as we look to your faithfulness and provision in the past, Lord, we know that we can trust you for the future.

124
00:09:46.880 --> 00:09:50.560
Lord, you did not spare your own son, but delivered him up for us all.

125
00:09:50.560 --> 00:09:54.120
How shall you not also with him freely give us all things?

126
00:09:54.800 --> 00:09:56.320
And so, you've done the greatest thing.

127
00:09:56.320 --> 00:10:00.080
So Lord, I pray that you would provide for them and guide them in the days ahead.

128
00:10:01.080 --> 00:10:06.560
Lord, I just pray for us now as we come to hear your word proclaimed.

129
00:10:06.680 --> 00:10:09.080
Lord, I pray that we would come with expectant hearts.

130
00:10:09.560 --> 00:10:14.120
Lord, I pray that you would provide what we need this morning through your servant as he brings your word.

131
00:10:14.560 --> 00:10:16.120
In Jesus' name. Amen.

132
00:10:16.720 --> 00:10:17.320
Amen.

133
00:10:18.600 --> 00:10:19.120
OK.

134
00:10:25.200 --> 00:10:26.000
Thanks, Brandon.

135
00:10:37.600 --> 00:10:40.680
Well, thank you very much for inviting me to be with you today.

136
00:10:40.680 --> 00:10:46.880
From the moment I heard that Brandon and Julia were planting a new church north of Birmingham,

137
00:10:47.320 --> 00:10:53.120
I've been rooting for you guys and praying for this church to be firmly established.

138
00:10:54.160 --> 00:11:03.160
We are going to be looking at the Bible passage printed on this page of their service program, service bulletin.

139
00:11:04.040 --> 00:11:06.560
And I will read that out now.

140
00:11:06.560 --> 00:11:11.160
I'm only going to go down as far as verse 15.

141
00:11:11.160 --> 00:11:14.800
There is nothing wrong with verses 16 through 21.

142
00:11:14.800 --> 00:11:15.880
Nothing wrong at all.

143
00:11:15.880 --> 00:11:20.960
But I'm only going to go as far as verse 15 today.

144
00:11:24.560 --> 00:11:29.360
John chapter two, verse 23 through chapter three, verse 15.

145
00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:33.840
Now, when he was in Jerusalem at the Passover feast,

146
00:11:34.480 --> 00:11:38.440
many believed in his name when they saw the signs that he was doing.

147
00:11:39.800 --> 00:11:45.960
But Jesus on his part did not entrust himself to them because he knew all people

148
00:11:46.520 --> 00:11:53.160
and needed no one to bear witness about man, for he himself knew what was in man.

149
00:11:55.160 --> 00:11:59.320
Now, there was a man of the Pharisees named Nicodemus, a ruler of the Jews.

150
00:11:59.760 --> 00:12:03.800
This man came to Jesus by night and said to him, Rabbi,

151
00:12:04.760 --> 00:12:07.720
we know that you are a teacher come from God,

152
00:12:08.600 --> 00:12:13.840
for no one can do these signs that you do unless God is with him.

153
00:12:14.680 --> 00:12:20.160
Jesus answered him, truly, truly, I say to you, unless one is born again,

154
00:12:21.120 --> 00:12:23.560
he cannot see the kingdom of God.

155
00:12:25.120 --> 00:12:27.680
Nicodemus said to him,

156
00:12:27.760 --> 00:12:30.040
how can a man be born when he is old?

157
00:12:30.720 --> 00:12:35.200
Can he enter a second time into his mother's womb and be born?

158
00:12:36.080 --> 00:12:43.800
Jesus answered, truly, truly, I say to you, unless one is born of water and the spirit,

159
00:12:44.320 --> 00:12:47.440
he cannot enter the kingdom of God.

160
00:12:48.240 --> 00:12:53.520
That which is born of the flesh is flesh, and that which is born of the spirit is spirit.

161
00:12:53.760 --> 00:12:58.680
Do not marvel that I said to you, you must be born again.

162
00:12:59.480 --> 00:13:02.760
The wind blows where it wishes and you hear its sound,

163
00:13:03.200 --> 00:13:06.800
but you do not know where it comes from or where it goes.

164
00:13:06.920 --> 00:13:11.440
So it is with everyone who is born of the spirit.

165
00:13:13.080 --> 00:13:16.640
Nicodemus said to him, how can these things be?

166
00:13:17.680 --> 00:13:20.480
Jesus answered him, are you the teacher of Israel?

167
00:13:20.480 --> 00:13:23.160
And yet you do not understand these things?

168
00:13:23.200 --> 00:13:26.920
Truly, truly, I say to you, we speak of what we know

169
00:13:27.600 --> 00:13:33.160
and bear witness to what we have seen, but you do not receive our testimony.

170
00:13:33.960 --> 00:13:37.440
If I have told you earthly things and you do not believe,

171
00:13:37.840 --> 00:13:41.040
how can you believe if I tell you heavenly things?

172
00:13:41.760 --> 00:13:48.200
No one has ascended into heaven except he who descended from heaven, the Son of man.

173
00:13:49.160 --> 00:13:52.200
And as Moses lifted up the serpent in the wilderness,

174
00:13:52.520 --> 00:13:55.320
so must the Son of man be lifted up

175
00:13:56.000 --> 00:14:00.680
that whoever believes in him may have eternal life.

176
00:14:02.200 --> 00:14:04.680
This is the word of the Lord.

177
00:14:04.680 --> 00:14:07.320
Thanks be to God.

178
00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:13.760
Well, before we start, please join me in praying for God's help.

179
00:14:13.760 --> 00:14:15.920
Let's bow our heads.

180
00:14:15.960 --> 00:14:19.160
In Jeremiah chapter 15, Jeremiah says to God,

181
00:14:19.640 --> 00:14:22.360
when your words came, I ate them.

182
00:14:22.920 --> 00:14:25.960
They were my joy and my heart's delight.

183
00:14:26.640 --> 00:14:29.720
Father, we pray that like Jeremiah,

184
00:14:30.120 --> 00:14:36.160
we would find that your words are our joy and our heart's delight.

185
00:14:36.640 --> 00:14:38.640
We ask this for Jesus' sake.

186
00:14:39.280 --> 00:14:40.280
Amen.

187
00:14:42.960 --> 00:14:45.120
Let me tell you about Adam.

188
00:14:45.240 --> 00:14:47.400
Adam was a friend of mine at high school.

189
00:14:48.240 --> 00:14:53.200
And it wouldn't surprise me if there was someone like him at your high school, too.

190
00:14:53.800 --> 00:14:57.920
Adam did everything the way it ought to be done.

191
00:14:59.120 --> 00:15:01.720
You always got a schoolwork handed in on time.

192
00:15:01.720 --> 00:15:04.960
He was never in trouble with his teachers.

193
00:15:04.960 --> 00:15:08.080
He was friendly to everyone and everyone liked him.

194
00:15:08.240 --> 00:15:13.360
His default facial expression was a cheerful smile.

195
00:15:13.800 --> 00:15:17.520
His clothes were always clean and tidy.

196
00:15:17.720 --> 00:15:19.880
When Adam reached his senior year,

197
00:15:19.880 --> 00:15:24.400
no one was surprised when the school gave him leadership responsibilities.

198
00:15:25.760 --> 00:15:28.920
Did you have an Adam at your high school?

199
00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:31.400
Maybe it was you.

200
00:15:31.400 --> 00:15:35.280
Maybe you are the kind of person who other people would think of

201
00:15:35.280 --> 00:15:40.160
in the way I think of Adam, the guy who did everything the way it ought to be done.

202
00:15:41.160 --> 00:15:46.000
Well, if we could ask the people who lived in Jerusalem 2000 years ago

203
00:15:46.000 --> 00:15:49.880
to think of someone like Adam, who they've known at high school,

204
00:15:49.880 --> 00:15:53.400
one name would instantly come to their minds, Nicodemus.

205
00:15:54.240 --> 00:15:57.760
He's introduced in chapter three, verse one.

206
00:15:57.760 --> 00:16:03.160
Now there was a man of the Pharisees named Nicodemus, a ruler of the Jews.

207
00:16:04.040 --> 00:16:07.040
We're told, first of all, that he's a Pharisee.

208
00:16:08.040 --> 00:16:11.120
And the Pharisees were famous for lawkeeping.

209
00:16:11.120 --> 00:16:14.440
Nicodemus would have spent all his waking hours

210
00:16:14.440 --> 00:16:19.960
thinking about God's commands and trying to obey them.

211
00:16:19.960 --> 00:16:22.360
The big ones do not murder, do not steal,

212
00:16:22.360 --> 00:16:25.080
but also the less well-known ones.

213
00:16:25.080 --> 00:16:30.680
Like Adam at my high school, Nicodemus never seemed to step out of line.

214
00:16:31.360 --> 00:16:34.200
We're also told in verse one of chapter three

215
00:16:34.200 --> 00:16:36.680
that Nicodemus was a ruler of the Jews.

216
00:16:36.920 --> 00:16:41.640
Only a few Pharisees were included on the Jewish ruling council,

217
00:16:41.640 --> 00:16:44.920
which means even among the Pharisees,

218
00:16:44.920 --> 00:16:49.080
Nicodemus stood out as one of their best men.

219
00:16:49.080 --> 00:16:52.920
He was Pharisee of the month again and again.

220
00:16:54.000 --> 00:16:56.000
There's something else we're told about Nicodemus,

221
00:16:56.000 --> 00:16:59.040
which is that he came to see Jesus at night.

222
00:16:59.880 --> 00:17:02.480
Why would he do that?

223
00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:03.120
Why would he do that?

224
00:17:03.120 --> 00:17:07.240
Why would he go to Jesus at night instead of during the day?

225
00:17:07.240 --> 00:17:11.400
It's something you do if you're meeting someone controversial

226
00:17:11.400 --> 00:17:15.160
and you think it's best if people don't know about that.

227
00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:19.160
They don't know that you're going to see this controversial person.

228
00:17:20.360 --> 00:17:23.680
At that time, Jesus was a controversial figure

229
00:17:23.680 --> 00:17:26.280
with a questionable reputation.

230
00:17:26.280 --> 00:17:30.280
Unlike Nicodemus, Jesus was considered unsound.

231
00:17:34.080 --> 00:17:37.800
So Nicodemus looks this way and that way to check.

