00:31:17.520 --> 00:31:20.000
If I have told you earthly things and you do not believe

494
00:31:20.000 --> 00:31:23.360
how can you believe if I tell you heavenly things?

495
00:31:23.360 --> 00:31:24.720
We'll pause there.

496
00:31:24.720 --> 00:31:28.800
That's build up what we've just heard, a drum roll.

497
00:31:28.800 --> 00:31:30.280
Jesus is saying to Nicodemus,

498
00:31:30.280 --> 00:31:32.640
are you sure you're ready for this?

499
00:31:32.640 --> 00:31:36.160
Then in verse 13, Jesus underlines his own credentials.

500
00:31:36.160 --> 00:31:38.960
He says, no one has ascended into heaven

501
00:31:38.960 --> 00:31:43.240
except he who descended from heaven, the Son of Man.

502
00:31:43.280 --> 00:31:45.000
Whenever Jesus talks about the Son of Man,

503
00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:46.120
he's talking about himself.

504
00:31:46.120 --> 00:31:48.640
So what he's saying in verse 13

505
00:31:48.640 --> 00:31:51.120
is that he knows what he's talking about

506
00:31:51.120 --> 00:31:56.120
because he's the only one who has come down from heaven.

507
00:31:57.120 --> 00:31:59.320
Then in verses 14 and 15,

508
00:31:59.320 --> 00:32:01.040
Jesus gets to the heart of the matter,

509
00:32:01.040 --> 00:32:03.520
the drum roll is over.

510
00:32:03.520 --> 00:32:08.160
This is the how of new life, verse 14.

511
00:32:08.160 --> 00:32:11.920
And as Moses lifted up the serpent in the wilderness,

512
00:32:11.920 --> 00:32:14.960
so must the Son of Man be lifted up

513
00:32:14.960 --> 00:32:19.960
that whoever believes in him may have eternal life.

514
00:32:22.320 --> 00:32:24.400
The part about the serpent in the wilderness

515
00:32:24.400 --> 00:32:26.080
is something that happened when the Israelites

516
00:32:26.080 --> 00:32:29.520
were on their way from Egypt to the promised land of Canaan.

517
00:32:29.520 --> 00:32:34.160
There was a sudden plague of venomous snakes along the way.

518
00:32:34.160 --> 00:32:37.000
They kept slithering into the Israelites tents.

519
00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:38.800
It was terrifying.

520
00:32:38.800 --> 00:32:42.640
One snake bite was a death sentence.

521
00:32:43.720 --> 00:32:47.160
But God gave the people a solution to that terrible problem.

522
00:32:47.160 --> 00:32:49.280
Moses was told to make a bronze snake

523
00:32:49.280 --> 00:32:50.960
and fix it to a pole.

524
00:32:50.960 --> 00:32:52.320
Here's a quote from the Old Testament.

525
00:32:52.320 --> 00:32:57.320
This is God talking about that bronze snake on the pole.

526
00:32:57.840 --> 00:33:01.800
God says, anyone who is bitten can look at it and live.

527
00:33:03.680 --> 00:33:07.360
Anyone who is bitten, God told the Israelites,

528
00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:09.600
can look at it and live.

529
00:33:09.600 --> 00:33:11.560
Moses then quickly made a bronze snake,

530
00:33:11.560 --> 00:33:14.440
put it on a pole and when anyone was bitten by a snake,

531
00:33:15.440 --> 00:33:19.560
and then looked at that bronze snake, that person lived.

532
00:33:19.560 --> 00:33:23.360
A look was enough to save.

533
00:33:23.360 --> 00:33:25.240
A look was enough to save.

534
00:33:25.240 --> 00:33:28.040
So in verse 15, Jesus is saying that the Son of Man,

535
00:33:28.040 --> 00:33:31.480
that's him, he is going to be lifted up

536
00:33:31.480 --> 00:33:34.200
like that snake in Moses' time.

537
00:33:34.200 --> 00:33:37.120
And that happened when Jesus was crucified,

538
00:33:37.120 --> 00:33:39.400
his hands and feet were nailed to the cross,

539
00:33:39.400 --> 00:33:43.800
which meant that his whole body was lifted up off the ground.

540
00:33:43.800 --> 00:33:46.600
And just as looking at the bronze snake,

541
00:33:46.600 --> 00:33:49.840
saved the snake bitten Israelites,

542
00:33:49.840 --> 00:33:54.840
so a look of faith at Christ crucified brings new life.

543
00:33:58.040 --> 00:34:02.280
It brings about the second birth.

544
00:34:02.280 --> 00:34:07.280
There is no new life without faith in Christ.

545
00:34:11.960 --> 00:34:14.680
My favorite movie is Master and Commander,

546
00:34:14.680 --> 00:34:17.320
starring Russell Crow.

547
00:34:17.320 --> 00:34:18.160
Anyone?

548
00:34:18.160 --> 00:34:19.000
Anyone?

549
00:34:19.000 --> 00:34:20.760
I've got one nodding head there.

550
00:34:21.760 --> 00:34:24.440
It's about Jack Aubrey, a ship's captain

551
00:34:24.440 --> 00:34:26.120
in the early 1800s.

552
00:34:26.120 --> 00:34:29.240
The movie is based on a series of novels

553
00:34:29.240 --> 00:34:32.840
and in most of those books, Captain Jack Aubrey

554
00:34:33.880 --> 00:34:36.560
chases after French or Spanish ships

555
00:34:36.560 --> 00:34:39.400
trying to win a great victory for the Royal Navy.

556
00:34:39.400 --> 00:34:41.960
In one of the books, the British ships

557
00:34:41.960 --> 00:34:45.120
have just caught sight of the French fleet.

558
00:34:46.240 --> 00:34:47.920
And the chase has begun.

559
00:34:48.960 --> 00:34:51.440
And the book says this about Jack Aubrey.

560
00:34:51.440 --> 00:34:54.040
His heart was bubbling high,

561
00:34:54.040 --> 00:34:58.160
that old splendid feeling of more,

562
00:34:58.280 --> 00:35:01.160
far more than common life.

563
00:35:01.160 --> 00:35:03.280
His heart was bubbling high,

564
00:35:03.280 --> 00:35:05.760
that old splendid feeling of more,

565
00:35:05.760 --> 00:35:08.080
far more than common life.

566
00:35:10.280 --> 00:35:13.560
John chapter three is telling us this morning,

567
00:35:13.560 --> 00:35:15.840
we don't need to join the Navy

568
00:35:15.840 --> 00:35:19.160
and leadership into battle against the French

569
00:35:19.160 --> 00:35:23.520
to have more, far more than common life.

570
00:35:23.520 --> 00:35:27.840
We can have abundant life, fullness of life,

571
00:35:27.840 --> 00:35:31.880
here and now in our current circumstances,

572
00:35:31.880 --> 00:35:33.520
through faith in Jesus.

573
00:35:35.000 --> 00:35:38.120
It's a life of love because born again people

574
00:35:38.120 --> 00:35:43.040
have a loving relationship with the risen Lord Jesus.

575
00:35:44.680 --> 00:35:46.880
Now behind the scenes that needs to be said,

576
00:35:46.880 --> 00:35:49.960
God is in charge of the new birth.

577
00:35:49.960 --> 00:35:53.680
God's sovereignty, His lordship over the whole process

578
00:35:53.680 --> 00:35:55.880
is seen at the start of verse eight

579
00:35:55.920 --> 00:36:00.520
where Jesus says, the wind blows where it wishes.

580
00:36:00.520 --> 00:36:02.920
That's Jesus' way of saying,

581
00:36:02.920 --> 00:36:07.920
we ourselves can't predict who will receive new life from God.

582
00:36:08.600 --> 00:36:10.240
It's God's decision.

583
00:36:11.600 --> 00:36:13.520
But from our point of view,

584
00:36:13.520 --> 00:36:16.560
new life begins when we look with faith

585
00:36:16.560 --> 00:36:19.920
at Jesus lifted up on the cross.

586
00:36:19.920 --> 00:36:23.480
A look of faith that Christ crucified

587
00:36:23.520 --> 00:36:27.560
brings a person all the blessings of the second birth.

588
00:36:27.560 --> 00:36:28.880
Have you done that yet?

589
00:36:28.880 --> 00:36:30.760
Have you looked?

590
00:36:30.760 --> 00:36:33.800
If you haven't, you could look with faith

591
00:36:33.800 --> 00:36:36.760
at Christ crucified today.

592
00:36:38.520 --> 00:36:40.320
Like those snake-bitten Israelites

593
00:36:40.320 --> 00:36:42.960
who looked at the bronze snake and were saved,

594
00:36:42.960 --> 00:36:47.000
if you look at Christ crucified with real faith,

595
00:36:47.000 --> 00:36:49.000
you will be born again.

596
00:36:51.480 --> 00:36:52.640
Maybe like Nicodemus,

597
00:36:52.640 --> 00:36:55.440
you've never realized that you need to be born again.

598
00:36:55.440 --> 00:36:59.040
Maybe you've been thinking that trying your best

599
00:36:59.040 --> 00:37:00.920
is the way to please God.

600
00:37:02.160 --> 00:37:07.000
If so, I hope Jesus' words have got through to you this morning.

601
00:37:07.000 --> 00:37:09.560
In our own nature, relying on our own strength,

602
00:37:09.560 --> 00:37:11.000
we can't please God.

603
00:37:11.000 --> 00:37:14.200
We keep falling short of the people,

604
00:37:14.200 --> 00:37:16.680
of being the people we really ought to be.

605
00:37:18.920 --> 00:37:20.000
We need God's help,

606
00:37:20.000 --> 00:37:23.240
or else we face His condemnation and punishment.

607
00:37:23.240 --> 00:37:27.520
We need God to take away our sins and give us His Spirit.

608
00:37:27.520 --> 00:37:31.640
Please, if you've always been on the outside looking in,

609
00:37:33.080 --> 00:37:37.600
look with faith today at Christ crucified.

610
00:37:39.000 --> 00:37:41.640
Being born again won't change you in every way.

611
00:37:41.640 --> 00:37:44.200
The same face will look back at you

612
00:37:44.200 --> 00:37:45.560
in the mirror each morning.

613
00:37:45.560 --> 00:37:48.480
You'll have the same likes and dislikes

614
00:37:48.480 --> 00:37:52.200
when it comes to breakfast cereals

615
00:37:52.200 --> 00:37:54.600
and college football teams.

616
00:37:54.600 --> 00:37:56.600
And even with a new heart,

617
00:37:56.600 --> 00:38:00.280
it is still challenging to live life God's way.

618
00:38:00.280 --> 00:38:04.880
Bad stuff that you used to find tempting

619
00:38:04.880 --> 00:38:07.880
will probably still be very tempting.

620
00:38:07.880 --> 00:38:12.880
But alongside the continuity, there will be real change.

621
00:38:13.120 --> 00:38:16.560
For example, you'll be able to fight temptation

622
00:38:16.560 --> 00:38:20.520
with new spiritual power that you didn't have before.

623
00:38:22.520 --> 00:38:26.440
Being born again is real change happening to regular people.

624
00:38:26.440 --> 00:38:30.240
It is not wishful thinking, it is not religious waffle.

625
00:38:30.240 --> 00:38:32.760
It is real change to regular people.

626
00:38:34.000 --> 00:38:36.600
Nicodemus himself seems to have got the message.

627
00:38:36.600 --> 00:38:38.560
Later in John's Gospel in chapter seven,

628
00:38:38.560 --> 00:38:41.520
when all the religious leaders are attacking Jesus,

629
00:38:41.520 --> 00:38:44.000
Nicodemus stands up for him.

630
00:38:44.000 --> 00:38:47.400
And after Jesus has died, Nicodemus comes alongside

631
00:38:47.400 --> 00:38:52.400
Joseph of Arimathea to give Jesus an honorable burial.

632
00:38:53.520 --> 00:38:55.680
We don't know for sure, but it certainly looks

633
00:38:55.680 --> 00:39:00.000
as if Nicodemus responded to Jesus' message with faith.

634
00:39:02.280 --> 00:39:04.320
We've thought about the why of the new birth,

635
00:39:04.320 --> 00:39:06.080
why it's necessary, we've thought about

636
00:39:06.080 --> 00:39:08.200
the what of the new birth.

637
00:39:08.200 --> 00:39:09.280
What is it?

638
00:39:09.280 --> 00:39:12.320
All our sins washed away, the spirit put in our hearts,

639
00:39:12.320 --> 00:39:15.960
and we've just been thinking about the how of the new birth,

640
00:39:15.960 --> 00:39:18.880
how it happens from our point of view,

641
00:39:18.880 --> 00:39:21.720
that look of faith at Christ crucified.

642
00:39:21.720 --> 00:39:24.920
I wanna finish with a message to those of us

643
00:39:24.920 --> 00:39:27.160
who have already been born again in the past.

644
00:39:27.160 --> 00:39:28.360
Praise God.

645
00:39:28.360 --> 00:39:31.600
Those of us who are confident that in his love,

646
00:39:31.600 --> 00:39:34.800
his great love, God has given us new life.

647
00:39:34.800 --> 00:39:38.120
That's most of us probably, or maybe all of us,

648
00:39:38.120 --> 00:39:40.120
here today, here is the message.

649
00:39:40.160 --> 00:39:43.720
Live out your new life.

650
00:39:43.720 --> 00:39:45.520
Live it out.

651
00:39:45.520 --> 00:39:48.120
Keep the new you activated.

652
00:39:48.120 --> 00:39:50.160
Don't settle back into the old you

653
00:39:50.160 --> 00:39:52.120
and your old way of life.

654
00:39:52.120 --> 00:39:57.120
We have power as God's reborn people to live life his way.

655
00:40:00.560 --> 00:40:03.360
He tells us about that new life in the Bible

656
00:40:03.360 --> 00:40:07.200
and he gives us the power we need to live it.

657
00:40:08.480 --> 00:40:10.000
How does that play out in practice?

658
00:40:10.000 --> 00:40:12.560
Well, when we're tempted to have yet another day

659
00:40:12.560 --> 00:40:17.560
without reading the Bible or spending time in prayer,

660
00:40:17.920 --> 00:40:22.040
we can live out our new life by asking God to help us,

661
00:40:23.080 --> 00:40:25.560
push social media to one side

662
00:40:25.560 --> 00:40:28.680
and devote some time to him alone,

663
00:40:28.680 --> 00:40:32.480
reading his word, listening to his voice and his word,

664
00:40:32.480 --> 00:40:33.400
praying to him.

665
00:40:34.680 --> 00:40:39.380
Or when we see someone in our church family with a need,

666
00:40:39.380 --> 00:40:43.300
we can live out our new life by serving that needy person,

667
00:40:43.300 --> 00:40:45.780
bearing their burdens.

668
00:40:45.780 --> 00:40:48.620
The old way of life is a shoulder shrugging,

669
00:40:48.620 --> 00:40:50.260
can't be bothered way of life,

670
00:40:50.260 --> 00:40:52.180
at least that's how it was for me,

671
00:40:52.180 --> 00:40:56.540
but born again people can rise above that by God's power.

672
00:40:56.540 --> 00:40:58.700
We have the spirit of God dwelling within us

673
00:40:58.700 --> 00:41:01.500
and he empowers us to live life God's way,

674
00:41:01.500 --> 00:41:04.560
bearing one another's burdens, loving one another.

675
00:41:05.620 --> 00:41:07.220
Another way to live out our new life

676
00:41:07.260 --> 00:41:10.260
is to live with hope instead of despair.

677
00:41:10.260 --> 00:41:13.480
America has been through a rough week

678
00:41:13.480 --> 00:41:16.660
and it's right for us to grieve when we see a public figure

679
00:41:16.660 --> 00:41:19.540
shot dead on a college campus.

680
00:41:19.540 --> 00:41:22.460
It's right for us to grieve, but we shouldn't despair.

681
00:41:23.600 --> 00:41:26.900
Born again people will see the kingdom of God,

682
00:41:26.900 --> 00:41:29.660
we'll enter into it and live there forever.

683
00:41:29.660 --> 00:41:34.260
That kingdom is coming and there will be no tears in it.

684
00:41:34.260 --> 00:41:37.660
It will be a place of perfect justice.

685
00:41:37.660 --> 00:41:40.660
Jesus will himself be there.

686
00:41:42.420 --> 00:41:45.500
As born again people, one of the ways in which we live out

687
00:41:45.500 --> 00:41:49.380
our new life is by looking forward to what is to come.

688
00:41:49.380 --> 00:41:52.220
Our hope isn't pinned to this world.

689
00:41:53.780 --> 00:41:57.300
We're citizens of heaven, the best is yet to come.

690
00:41:57.300 --> 00:41:59.460
New heavens and a new earth.

691
00:42:00.620 --> 00:42:03.940
What will it mean for you to activate the new you

692
00:42:03.940 --> 00:42:08.940
to live it out, this born again you during the week ahead?

693
00:42:10.540 --> 00:42:13.900
What might be different for you if you live out

694
00:42:13.900 --> 00:42:16.540
this new life instead of settling for the old way

695
00:42:16.540 --> 00:42:18.260
of doing things?

696
00:42:18.260 --> 00:42:23.260
Born again Christian, you have power from God

697
00:42:23.260 --> 00:42:25.580
to live life his way.

698
00:42:26.500 --> 00:42:31.340
Make use of that power to the glory of Jesus Christ.

699
00:42:32.460 --> 00:42:33.300
Let's pray.

700
00:42:34.940 --> 00:42:38.940
Father in heaven, we thank you for making it possible for us

701
00:42:38.940 --> 00:42:42.940
to be born again through the sacrificial death

702
00:42:42.940 --> 00:42:47.940
of your son Jesus and by sending your spirit.

703
00:42:49.660 --> 00:42:53.820
Help us Father to live out this new life you've given us.

704
00:42:55.060 --> 00:42:58.020
Help us to keep it activated day by day.

705
00:42:59.740 --> 00:43:02.220
And if there's anyone here not yet born again,

706
00:43:02.900 --> 00:43:07.900
please give them this new life in your grace and mercy.

707
00:43:09.860 --> 00:43:14.380
Help that person look with faith at Christ crucified.

708
00:43:14.380 --> 00:43:15.220
Amen.

